I"]<h2 id="welcome">Welcome!</h2>

<p>I am a Ph.D. candidate in Economics at the University of Bonn and a research fellow at the Institute of Finance and Statistics at the University of Bonn. I am interested in Econometrics and Statistics, specifically in Nonparametric Statistics and Time Series Analysis. I am also interested in economic applications for statistical methods. You can find the short version of my CV <a href="http://localhost:4000/download/CV_short.pdf">here</a>, my Job Market Paper <a href="http://localhost:4000/download/epidemic_paper.pdf">here</a>, and an overview of my research <a href="http://localhost:4000/research">here</a>.</p>

<p>I will be available for interviews at the EEA’s and AEA’s online job market meetings.</p>

<p><strong>References:</strong> <a href="https://mivogt.github.io/"> Prof. Dr. Michael Vogt </a> (University of Ulm), <a href="http://www.statistik.uni-bonn.de/members/prof-dr-a-kneip/?L=1"> Prof. Dr. Alois Kneip </a> (University of Bonn), <a href="https://sites.google.com/view/joachimfreyberger/home"> Prof. Dr. Joachim Freyberger </a> (University of Bonn)</p>
